<task id="049" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-B-10 Phase B exit-gate validation (4 exit criteria from spec)</title>
    <phase>Phase B — Schema-Aware Output</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1-2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>048</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
    <tags>docs</tags>
    <rigor-hint>MINIMAL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Documentation gate — verifies + records that Phase B exit criteria are met from already-captured evidence. No code change. MINIMAL rigor per Step 3.5.5 decision tree.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Phase exit gate — sequentially after integration test (task 048).</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Validate the 4 Phase B exit criteria from `spec.md` §Phase B Exit Criteria using
    evidence already captured in task 048 + tasks 030-042 notes. This task is a
    documentation gate: it does NOT re-run scenarios, it composes a Phase B exit-gate
    report citing per-criterion evidence references. The 4 criteria are:

    1. Workspace renderer handles array-typed (`tldr`) fields correctly (bulleted list,
       not raw JSON).
    2. Workspace renderer handles object-typed (`entities`) fields correctly (labeled
       groups, not raw JSON literal).
    3. `outputSchema` declared on action; destination/widgetType on node config (Q5
       re-shape).
    4. Duplicate-fire eliminated at CapabilityRouter (typing `/summarize` produces ONE
       render).

    For each criterion: cite evidence reference (e.g.,
    `notes/task-048-phase-b-integration-evidence.md` scenario X; `task-040 widget
    implementation evidence`; `task-042 dedup refactor evidence`). Record exit-gate
    decision in `notes/phase-b-exit-gate-report.md`. If any criterion is not met based
    on evidence: STOP, escalate, and do NOT mark Phase B exited.

    Phase B exit gate requires user sign-off per CLAUDE.md Confirmation Triggers. After
    composing the report, pause and present to user for explicit go/no-go to Phase C.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Comfortable composing crisp exit-gate reports from
    already-captured evidence. No code work — pure documentation + escalation.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/phase-b-exit-gate-report.md`
    exists with per-criterion verdict (PASS / FAIL / EVIDENCE-MISSING) and evidence
    references. If all 4 criteria PASS: Phase B is exit-ready. User sign-off captured
    (per CLAUDE.md Confirmation Triggers — phase exit gates require user sign-off).
    TASK-INDEX.md updated. Project ready to begin Phase C (Tri-directional Workspace +
    Memory + Visibility) once user approves.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
