      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Phase B closes the Pillar 5 work (schema-aware output) — a tight architectural
      slice that fixes R5 SC-18 rendering bugs + duplicate-fire structurally. With
      Phase B exited, Phase C (Pillar 6 + 7 + 9 — tri-directional workspace state +
      memory + visibility) begins. Phase B exit is a CLAUDE.md Confirmation Trigger
      requiring user sign-off.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/phase-b-exit-gate-report.md (NEW)</file>
    </relevant-files>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 048 produced the integration evidence this task consumes.</item>
      <item>Tasks 030-042 produced per-task evidence references this task cites.</item>
      <item>Phase A exit gate (Phase A task) is the pattern reference for this report's shape.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: MINIMAL
      📋 REASON: Documentation gate; cites evidence; no code change
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS: 5 steps; Step 9.5 quality gates SKIPPED per MINIMAL rigor
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress + Gather Evidence">
      Read TASK-INDEX.md; confirm 049 status 🔲; dep (048) complete. Read every file in
      &lt;inputs&gt; — verify all referenced evidence files exist with substantive content.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Verify Exit Criteria Per Spec">
      Open `spec.md` § Phase B Exit Criteria. Per criterion:
      (1) Array-typed (`tldr`) handled correctly — cite task 040 evidence + task 048
          Scenario 1.
      (2) Object-typed (`entities`) handled correctly — cite task 041 evidence + task 048
          Scenario 2.
      (3) `outputSchema` on action + destination/widgetType on node config — cite tasks
          030, 031, 032, 033, 034, 035 evidence.
      (4) Duplicate-fire eliminated at CapabilityRouter — cite task 042 evidence + task
          048 Scenario 3.

      Also verify: cumulative BFF publish-size delta across Phase B is within ≤+5 MB R6
      total budget per NFR-02 — sum task-by-task deltas from notes.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Verify NFR-07 Pre-Fill Regression">
      Confirm tasks 034 + 035 evidence shows ZERO drift in per-field wizard output
      values vs BEFORE baselines (NFR-07 binding). Cite task 048 Scenarios 4 + 5 for
      end-to-end re-verification.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Compose Phase B Exit-Gate Report">
      Create `notes/phase-b-exit-gate-report.md`:
      - Phase B exit criteria summary (per-criterion PASS / FAIL / EVIDENCE-MISSING + reference)
      - Cumulative BFF publish-size delta vs budget
      - NFR-07 pre-fill binding confirmation
      - R5 Gap A structural fix confirmation
      - Concluding recommendation: GO / NO-GO to Phase C
      - Outstanding risks (if any)

      If any FAIL or EVIDENCE-MISSING: stop here; escalate to user.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="User Sign-Off + Complete">
      Present the report to the user. PAUSE for explicit go/no-go decision per CLAUDE.md
      Confirmation Triggers. On GO: update TASK-INDEX.md: 049 🔲 → ✅; reset
      `current-task.md` to the first pending Phase C task. On NO-GO: keep 049 in
      progress; address blockers per user direction.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="git">Stage + commit the exit-gate report on R6 worktree branch</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/phase-b-exit-gate-report.md (NEW — per-criterion verdict + evidence + go/no-go)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status 049 🔲 → ✅; Phase B summary row marked complete)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/current-task.md (reset to first pending Phase C task)</output>
    <output type="report">Task completion report citing user sign-off</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`notes/phase-b-exit-gate-report.md` exists with per-criterion verdict (4 criteria) + evidence reference + cumulative BFF size delta + NFR-07 confirmation + R5 Gap A confirmation + go/no-go recommendation.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 4 Phase B exit criteria verdict = PASS (citing task 040 + 041 + 042 + 048 evidence; tasks 030-035 supporting).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Cumulative BFF publish-size delta across Phase B reported and within ≤+5 MB R6 total budget per NFR-02.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NFR-07 pre-fill binding confirmed honored via task 048 Scenarios 4 + 5 evidence.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">R5 Gap A (path A vs path B parallelism is a smell) structurally fixed via task 042 + task 048 Scenario 3 evidence.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">User explicitly approved go-to-Phase-C per CLAUDE.md Confirmation Triggers (or NO-GO blockers documented and addressed).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX.md updated (049 🔲 → ✅; Phase B summary marked complete) and `current-task.md` reset to first pending Phase C task.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
